choice.explanation:
The synthesis should

1. introduce the tert‑butyl group first (needs an activated ring);
2. use a para‑sulfonic acid “blocking” group so that the first nitration can occur only ortho to the tert‑butyl group;
3. convert that ortho nitro group to a diazonium ion that will later become the phenolic oxygen;
4. with the para position still blocked, carry out a second nitration that now installs the final nitro group at the other ortho position (3‑position with respect to the future ethoxy group);  
5. hydrolyze the diazonium to the phenol, remove the sulfonic acid (desulfonation), and O‑alkylate to the ethyl ether.

The only option that follows this strategy and keeps functional groups compatible with each step is option C.

ANSWER: C

